,"text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sixalapN","text_ar":"سِخَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is extr. [as a pl. form, so much so that Sb holds it to be a quasi-pl. measure, not a broken pl. measure, as is said in the TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaA^apN","text_ar":"جِبَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","M","O","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}